==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Filthy
<hw>Filth"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Filthier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Filthiest</adjf>.]</amorph> <def>Defiled with filth, whether
material or moral; nasty; dirty; polluted; foul; impure; obscene.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧In the <xex>filthy</xex>-mantled pool.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He which is <qex>filthy</qex> let him be <qex>filthy</qex>
still.</q> <rj><qau>Rev. xxii. 11.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Nasty; foul; dirty; squalid; unclean; sluttish;
gross; vulgar; licentious. See <er>Nasty</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Filtrate</ent>⟦br⟧
